text: I'm a firm believer that if you read
something it's almost always more
delicious and in the case of zucchini I
can pretty much guarantee that it is I
mean I'm not saying anything against
zucchini but if you coat it with a
combination of Parmesan cheese and panko
breadcrumbs like I'm gonna do today and
bake it in the oven it's a guaranteed
crowd-pleaser start off by cutting your
zucchini into wedges I would say make
them about three inches long
approximately have your oven preheating
to 425 degrees you want a kind of
highest temperature to get them nice and
crisp in the oven I have one and a half
cups of panko breadcrumbs in this baking
dish and to that I'm going to add 3/4 of
a cup of grated Parmesan cheese the high
ratio of cheese for our high ratio of
deliciousness one-and-a-half teaspoons
of Italian seasoning you could use
oregano too if you wanted quarter
teaspoon of cayenne pepper 3/4 of a
teaspoon of coarse salt and a quarter
teaspoon of pepper
that's your breading mixture and then to
get the breading to it here you need
some egg and today I'm just going to use
egg white just using the egg white will
cut down on the fat
just whisk the egg white to break it up
a little bit then add your zucchini to
the egg white you can do a few pieces at
a time turn them to coat and then coat
them in the breadcrumbs and have about
two baking sheets sprayed with vegetable
spray you want to make sure that these
bake in a single layer you're going to
want to bake these at 425 degrees
turning once until they're golden brown
